# Potato Cheese Soup

> Pepe’s recipe as best we can figure. #soup #comfort

![](F2BD3E61-FF9C-4F70-9F0B-F739F5F01CEE.jpeg)

- Potato | Red, 6 | Peeled and diced into 1/2 inch cubes
- Garlic | 3 cloves | 2 Whole, 1 minced
- Vegetable Oil | 2 tbsp | 
- Salt | To taste | 

Lightly brown potatoes and garlic in a stock pot with oil over medium heat. Season with salt.

- Tomato Sauce | 15 oz can | 
- Water | 2 cans | 
- Dried Oregano | 1 tsp | 
- Garlic Powder | 1 tsp | 
- Onion Powder | 1 tsp | 
- Salt | to taste | 
- Black Pepper | to taste | 

Bring to a boil and let simmer until potatoes are cooked to desired doneness.

- Cheese | Colby or Longhorn, 8oz | Cut into 1/2” cubes

Take the soup off the heat and add half the cheese and stir. Let sit for 5 minutes.

Ladle into bowls and top with extra cheese to your liking.
